:: Begin exploring the mountain {"position":"1000,500","size":"100,100"}
As the litte figure arrived at the peak, a light suddenly welcomed the little one's eyes and fills the sky with life and clarity.

Soon enough, a voice echoes across the sky.

“Who dares step foot into my blessed land?”

The light shifts and reveals a small duck standing alone on its little feet.

How will the duck respond back?

[[Quack?]] 
[[Quack.]]
[[Quack!]]




:: Continue listening {"position":"1400,500","size":"100,100"}
The deity floats higher above the duck, the little one focusing its sight on the higher being.

“Standing before you is the divine protector of this sacred mountain of utmost purity..."

The light suddenly transforms into a majestic human form of a masculine figure, draped in fine pearl silk and bedazzled with striking diamonds.

"I am Bojinki, the celestial guardian of this peak. This place I hold dear does not allow trespassers without offerings worthy of this land.”

After gently landing on the mountain, Bojinki raised a hand at the level of his chest, signaling a command at his will.

The ground trembles as it soon reveals a stone altar, resembling a refined sculpted figure of an angel with its hands cupped together.

“One must offer something of value… or face my judgment.”

The altar glows faintly, waiting, as Bojinki stands firm with daunting eyes.

What would you, a mere duck, do to appease the mountain deity?

[[Gift a sacrificial offering]]
[[Offer a sentiment]]
[[Don't offer anything]]


:: Don't offer anything {"position":"1600,700","size":"100,100"}
The duck steps back and offers nothing.

The altar turned dark.

“You give nothing at all…” the deity murmurs.

The air feels tense. The atmosphere grows darker as the deity lifts the duck with unseen force.

"You bear no shame at a place where you don't belong."

Bojinki then drops the small creature roughly to the ground. The duck felt minimal pain from the short fall, but slowly stands back up, shaking the dust off from its feathers.

The deity still seems to show no signs of leaving, and doesn't seem happy with the duck's behavior. In this regard, the little one feels that it's still not the right time to leave for now.

[[Step away from the altar]]


:: Gift a sacrificial offering {"position":"1600,300","size":"100,100"}
The duck plucks one of its feathers and places it on the altar.

The stone absorbs it, glowing softly as the offering vanishes.

“You give what you can hold,” the deity says.

The air hums quietly.

The deity still seems to show no signs of leaving, but is amused with offering given. Regardless, the little one feels that it's still not the right time to leave for now.

[[Step away from the altar]] 


:: Hear the final judgment {"position":"2200,500","size":"100,100"}
The light softens.

“Your journey ends here,” the deity says.

“But what you revealed will follow you.”

The mountain grows quiet again as the deity slowly fades out of the scene.

Now greeted by silence once more, the duck feels different, changed by what it has done.

Whether it was fear, courage, kindness, or defiance, the choices it made now belong to it.

Slowly, the duck turns and begins its long walk back down the mountain, carrying the weight of its journey into the world beyond.

''The End''


:: Move forward without hesitation {"position":"2000,600","size":"100,100"}
The duck strides forward without hesitation.

The mist parts quickly before it.

“You do not hesitate,” the deity observes.

"With that, this item shall serve you well."

The duck is given something.

The bridge dissolves beneath the duck’s feet, returning it safely to the summit.

The duck stands once more before the glowing deity.

“I have seen enough.”

[[Hear the final judgment]]


:: Offer a sentiment {"position":"1600,500","size":"100,100"}
The duck closes its eyes and offers a deep feeling from within.

It shares its thoughts as the deity absorbs them. Words of sincere gratitude could be heard from the small creature, how being able to witness the higher being's presence is an honor and setting foot in its blessed premises brings joy and fulfillment.

The altar glows brighter.

“You give what you feel,” Bojinki says quietly.

A gentle warmth spreads through the summit.

The deity still seems to show no signs of leaving, but is pleased with the offered sentiment. Despite the outcome, the little one feels that it's still not the right time to leave for now.

[[Step away from the altar]] 


